docs.description: The submitted PDF was found to contain less than two pages, and a domain classified as malicious by Umbrella was contacted. The combination of these two behaviours is highly suspicious and is indicative of phishing or malicious activity by the PDF.
docs.title: pdf-malicious-uri-low-pages

docs.description: A domain referenced during the sample run has been categorized as phishing by Cisco Umbrella. Cisco Umbrella is a cloud security platform which provides additional detail about network activity such as security and content categorization for domains. Domains involved in phishing campaigns will often host web pages that attempt to steal user passwords, or other sensitive data. A phishing domain will host a web page that looks legitimate (like a banking login page) and if a user is tricked into entering their username and password, those credentials will be stolen.
docs.title: network-dns-category-phishing

docs.description: The submitted document was seen establishing outbound network communications. This activity could simply be embedded code that is reaching out to the vendor to check if it is running the latest version. However, it is more likely that this activity is malicious in nature. Attackers leverage vulnerabilities inside document types to establish a foothold into a victim's network. Once the system is exploited, embedded code will be executed that will download the second stage of the attack. Most often the second stage that is downloaded is a customized backdoor such as a Remote Access Trojan (RAT).
docs.title: document-network-traffic

docs.description: A domain which is present in a Cisco Umbrella block list was referenced during the analysis of the sample. Cisco Umbrella is a cloud security platform which provides additional detail about network activity such as security and content categorization for domains. Domains in the Cisco Umbrella block list are typically created to be part of a malware campaign and must reach a certain threshold of malicious activity before Cisco Umbrella will add it to the block list.
docs.title: network-opendns-malicious

docs.description: A document was seen contacting a domain that has been flagged by Cisco Umbrella as having suspicious or malicious content, or was newly registered. Documents often contact external domains for additional content. However, the fact that the domain is classified as potentially harmful or new is indicative of malicious behaviour.
docs.title: network-dns-doc-network-traffic
